Columns: 2;
                                                  ruled lines: 22;
                                                  written lines: 22; Samuel, Kings, Ezekiel, Joel, Micah and Haggai begin a new column, and Isaiah commences a new leaf. The margin of the manuscript contains the ḳeri and the beginning of the Hafṭarot. The titles of the books are written at the top of every recto and the leaves are numbered with Hebrew letters.Pricking and ruling (of bifolios, with hard-point on the hair-side) visible. Visible difference between flesh and hair side.
